# =============================================================
#  .gitattributes — Cross-platform line ending safety
#  File: .gitattributes (repository root)
#
#  WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#  ─────────────────────
#  CK3 on Windows, Mac, and Linux all accept LF (\n) line endings
#  in script/YAML files.  Windows Git defaults to converting LF
#  to CRLF (\r\n) on checkout — which CK3 does NOT handle well
#  (it may silently misparse events and ignore entries).
#
#  This file forces all text files in this repo to always use
#  LF line endings on all platforms.
#
#  HOW IT WORKS:
#  ─────────────
#  * = text=auto eol=lf  — every text file gets LF on checkout
#  *.yml text eol=lf     — YAML (localization) files always LF
#  *.txt text eol=lf     — CK3 script files always LF
#
#  ADDITIONAL NOTE — UTF-8 BOM:
#  ─────────────────────────────
#  CK3 YAML localization files (.yml) MUST also have a UTF-8 BOM
#  (bytes 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF at the start of the file).  This file
#  only controls line endings, not BOM.  All .yml files in
#  mod/localization/english/ have been saved with BOM.
#  If you create a new .yml file, add the BOM manually or via
#  your editor's "Save as UTF-8 with BOM" option.
# =============================================================

*       text=auto eol=lf

# CK3 script files
*.txt   text eol=lf

# CK3 localization YAML files
*.yml   text eol=lf

# Markdown documentation
*.md    text eol=lf

# Keep binary files untouched
*.dds   binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.tga   binary
*.ogg   binary
*.wav   binary
